BE IT ENACTED BY THE PEOPLE OF THE STATE OF OKLAHOMA:
12
13
SECTION 1. NEW LAW A new section of law to be codified
13
14
in the Oklahoma Statutes as Section 7501 of Title 36, unless there
14
15
is created a duplication in numbering, reads as follows:
15
16
A. As used in this act:
16
17
1. “Anesthesia services” means the same as defined by the
17
18
prevailing medical coding and billing standards in the professional
18
19
medical billing community, including the most recent version of the
19
20
Current Procedural Terminology (CPT) code books, the Medicare Claims
20
21
Processing Manual, and American Society of Anesthesiologists
21
22
guidance;
22
23
2. “Health benefit plan” means any plan that provides benefits
23
24
for medical or surgical expenses or disease management incurred as a
24
