1
result of a health condition, accident, or sickness, including an
1
2
individual, group, blanket, or franchise insurance policy or
2
3
insurance agreement, a group hospital service contract, or an
3
4
individual or group evidence of coverage or similar coverage
4
5
document that is issued by:
5
6
a. an insurance company,
6
7
b. a group hospital service corporation,
7
8
c. a health maintenance organization,
8
9
d. an approved nonprofit health corporation,
9
10
e. a small employer health benefit plan, or
10
11
f. any other health insurance company whose primary
11
12
purpose is to provide benefits for medical or surgical
12
13
expenses as a result of a health condition, accident,
13
14
sickness, or disease; and
14
15
3. “Physical status modifiers” means classifications set forth
15
16
in the American Society of Anesthesiologists (ASA) Physical Status
16
17
Classification System.
17
18
B. All health benefit plans shall consider the following
18
19
factors in determining necessity of services and calculation of
19
20
benefit payment amounts for anesthesia services:
20
21
1. The assessment of patient physical status, including the use
21
22
of physical status modifiers as determined by a participant’s
22
23
treating physician or health care provider; and
23
24
24
Req. No. 3413 Page 2

1
2. The complexity and urgency of care, as determined by a
1
2
participant’s treating physician or health care provider.
